==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chyle
<hw>Chyle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>chylus</ets>,
Gr. <?/ juice, chyle, fr. <?/ to pour: cf. F. <ets>chyle</ets>; prob.
akin to E. <ets>fuse</ets> to melt.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>A
milky fluid containing the fatty matter of the food in a state of
emulsion, or fine mechanical division; formed from chyme by the action
of the intestinal juices. It is absorbed by the lacteals, and conveyed
into the blood by the thoracic duct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chylifaction</ent>⟦br⟧
